  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>The hotel offers a half board basis which includes breakfast, afternoon tea and evening meals with wine included.</p>
<p><strong>Breakfast </strong></p>
<p><span data-contrast="auto">A continental buffet breakfast is available on 7 mornings of your holiday. There’ll be a selectio</span><span data-contrast="auto">n of cereals, bread and pastries from a local bakery, jams and spreads, local cheeses and charcuterie, yogurts and fresh fruits. There's coffee, teas, infusions, hot chocolates and fruit juices to choose from. </span><span data-ccp-props="{&quot;134233117&quot;:false,&quot;134233118&quot;:false,&quot;201341983&quot;:0,&quot;335551550&quot;:1,&quot;335551620&quot;:1,&quot;335559685&quot;:0,&quot;335559737&quot;:0,&quot;335559738&quot;:0,&quot;335559739&quot;:160,&quot;335559740&quot;:279}"> </span></p>
<p><span data-contrast="auto">For 6 mornings of your holiday there’s a classic full cooked breakfast available. Options can include free range eggs, sausages, bacon, halloumi, mushrooms and tomatoes.</span></p>
<p><strong>Afternoon Tea </strong></p>
<p><span data-contrast="auto">Homemade sweet and savoury options are baked each day and are ready for your return from the slopes, 6 days of the week. This includes soup, sandwiches, scones and cakes, all are perfect to pair with the selection of teas, hot chocolate and coffee, that’re available for you whenever you fancy.</span></p>
<p><strong>Evening Meal </strong></p>
<p><span data-contrast="auto">An exclusive 5-course evening meals with a choice of menu, is served on </span><span data-contrast="auto">6 evenings of your holiday. You’ll start your evening with a glass of prosecco and canapes</span><span data-contrast="auto">, where we have a choice of 2 Italian Proseccos from the Veneto region, one of which is a 0% alcohol option.</span></p>
<p><span data-contrast="none">There's a selection of 3 starters, mains and desserts, where you will make your choice in the morning and book your time of your meal between 7:30 - 9pm. The evening menu has been designed to incorporate a variety of different cuisines, including classic French, Asian, Italian and British dishes.</span></p>
<p><span data-contrast="none">After each homemade dessert there’s a selection of cheeses with fresh bread, crackers and chutney, along with coffee, tea or infusions.</span><span data-ccp-props="{&quot;134233117&quot;:false,&quot;134233118&quot;:false,&quot;201341983&quot;:0,&quot;335559738&quot;:240,&quot;335559739&quot;:240,&quot;335559740&quot;:279}"> </span></p>
<p><span data-contrast="auto">There will be special celebration menus on Christmas Day &amp; New Year's Eve.</span><span data-ccp-props="{&quot;201341983&quot;:0,&quot;335559685&quot;:0,&quot;335559739&quot;:160,&quot;335559740&quot;:279}"> </span></p>
<p><strong>Wine and Drinks </strong></p>
<p><span data-contrast="none">During your evening meal guests can indulge in our carefully selected complimentary local wines, which consists of a choice of 3 red, 3 white and 1 rosé. All of the wines have been carefully chosen so that there is a great variety and offer something to cater for all tastes and that pairs well with the menu.</span><span data-ccp-props="{&quot;134233117&quot;:false,&quot;134233118&quot;:false,&quot;201341983&quot;:0,&quot;335559738&quot;:240,&quot;335559739&quot;:240,&quot;335559740&quot;:279}"> </span></p>
<p>There's also a premium wine list available, if you would like to upgrade on the night.</p>
<p> </p>
<div class="white_box_shadow" style="text-align: center;">
<p><a name="savoie-menu"></a><strong>Hotel Le Savoie Sample Menu</strong></p>
<p><strong><strong>APÉRITIF</strong></strong></p>
<p>A glass of Prosecco<br /><span style="color: #fcaf17; font-size: 10px;">★<span style="color: #fcaf17; font-size: 10px;">★</span>★★★</span><br /><strong>CHOICE OF </strong><strong>STARTERS</strong></p>
<p>Twice Baked Cheese Soufflé</p>
<p>Prawn Linguine in "XO Sauce" and Parmesan</p>
<p>Beef Carpaccio, Caramelised Fig, Mozzarella and Watercress<br /><span style="color: #fcaf17; font-size: 10px;">★<span style="color: #fcaf17; font-size: 10px;">★</span>★★★</span><br /><strong>CHOICE OF </strong><strong>MAIN COURSES</strong></p>
<p>Lamb Shoulder, Jerusalem Artichoke, Goats Curd, Beetroot, Jus</p>
<p>Tuna, Braised Fennel and Beurre-Blanc Sauce</p>
<p><strong>SIDES</strong></p>
<p>Caesar Salad</p>
<p>Crushed Herb Potatoes</p>
<p><strong>VEGETARIAN OPTION</strong></p>
<p>Wild Mushroom Risotto, Truffle and Parmesan</p>
<p><span style="color: #fcaf17; font-size: 10px;">★<span style="color: #fcaf17; font-size: 10px;">★</span>★★★</span><br /><strong>CHOICE OF</strong> <strong>DESSERTS</strong></p>
<p>Tart Tatin with Vanilla Bean Ice-cream</p>
<p>Lemon Curd, Meringue, Biscuit Crumble</p>
<p>Chocolate Lava Cake with Vanilla Bean Ice-cream</p>
<p><span style="color: #fcaf17; font-size: 10px;">★<span style="color: #fcaf17; font-size: 10px;">★</span>★★★</span><br /><strong><strong>SELECTION OF FRENCH CHEESES AND PETIT FOURS<br /></strong></strong><span style="color: #fcaf17; font-size: 10px;">★<span style="color: #fcaf17; font-size: 10px;">★</span>★★★</span><br /><strong><strong>CHOCOLATE TRUFFLE SELECTION &amp; COFFEE OF CHOICE</strong></strong><br /><span style="color: #fcaf17; font-size: 10px;">★<span style="color: #fcaf17; font-size: 10px;">★</span>★★★</span><br /><strong>A CHOICE OF A QUALITY SELECTION OF COMPLIMENTARY RED, WHITE &amp; ROSÉ WINES</strong></p>
</div>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Please note </strong></p>
<p><span data-contrast="auto">Breakfast hot option, afternoon tea &amp; dinner is 6 days per week due to staff's day off. Our representatives are there to recommend and book a local restaurant in resort for the free evening. </span><span data-ccp-props="{&quot;134233117&quot;:false,&quot;134233118&quot;:false,&quot;201341983&quot;:0,&quot;335559738&quot;:240,&quot;335559739&quot;:240,&quot;335559740&quot;:279}"> </span></p>
<p><span data-ccp-props="{&quot;134233117&quot;:false,&quot;134233118&quot;:false,&quot;201341983&quot;:0,&quot;335559738&quot;:240,&quot;335559739&quot;:240,&quot;335559740&quot;:279}">Staff day off is usually a Wednesday, but for Christmas and New Year week this will be a Thursday.</span></p>]]></cateringDescription>
